cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.DS 

The paper introduces a Bayesian nonparametric stochastic block model for network data that allows entities associated with each node to have mixed membership in an unbounded collection of latent communities. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including social and information networks (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), systems and control (cs.SY), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and statistical learning (cs.SD). However, given the focus on network data and the use of regression models to predict node metadata, cs.SI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories.
